External Integrations

Purpose: Client wrappers and adapters for third-party external services and APIs.

What belongs here:
- Third-party REST API clients (payment gateways, SMS providers, email services)
- Cloud storage adapters (AWS S3, Azure Blob, Google Cloud Storage)
- External authentication provider clients (OAuth2, SAML, OpenID Connect)
- Webhook sender and receiver utilities
- External service DTOs and response models
- Retry policy and circuit breaker helpers for external calls
- External API configuration and credential management

Design rules:
- Each external service gets its own unit or subfolder.
- Never hardcode external service credentials; use configuration or environment variables.
- Wrap all external calls in try/except; external failures must not crash the server.
- Use TRequestAPI (from shared/clients/) as the base HTTP client where possible.
- Implement timeout handling for all external calls.
- Log external call failures with enough context for debugging but without exposing secrets.

